import os
import pandas as pd

# Get each data file from Jim Weller's dataset
datapath = "/Users/hawk/Documents/DOCUMENTS/School/2014S/CMPSC440/Lab5/data"

def get_files(run):
    datafiles = {}
    runpath = (datapath + "/" + run)
    files = [f for f in os.listdir(runpath) if ('.csv' in f and "jobQueue.csv" not in f)]
    # loop through & load the data files -> Pandas data frames
    for filename in files:
        filepath = runpath + "/" + filename
        datafiles[run+"_"+filename] = pd.read_csv(filepath,
                                                  header=1,
                                                  skiprows=range(52,57))
    return pd.concat(datafiles)

jim   = get_files("jim")
rand1 = get_files("rand1")
rand2 = get_files("rand2")
rand3 = get_files("rand3")
rand4 = get_files("rand4")
rand5 = get_files("rand5")

##########################
# VIZ/ANALYSIS FUNCTIONS #
##########################
texstr = "Wait time &\t\t{wmean} &\t{wdev} &\t{wmin} &\t{wmax} \t\\\\\nResponse time &\t\t{rmean} &\t{rdev} &\t{rmin} &\t{rmax} \t\\\\\nTurnaround time &\t{tmean} &\t{tdev} &\t{tmin} &\t{tmax} \t\\\\"

def table (df):
    """Prints describe() tables for each algorithm"""
    for name in filenames(df):
        print(name + "\n-------------------------------------")
        print(df.xs(name, 0).describe())
        print("\n")
        
def textable(df):
    """Prints tables for each algorithm, ready to be pasted into a LaTeX Tabular environment"""
    for name in filenames(df):
        print(name +"\n\t\t\tmean\tstd.dev\t\tmin\tmax")
        print("\t\t\t----\t-------\t\t---\t---")
        print(texstr.format(
                            # wait time stats
                            wmean = np.mean(df.xs(name,0)["Wait"]),
                            wdev  = np.std(df.xs(name,0)["Wait"]),
                            wmin  = np.amin(df.xs(name,0)["Wait"]),
                            wmax  = np.amin(df.xs(name,0)["Wait"]),
                            # response time stats
                            rmean = np.mean(df.xs(name,0)["Response"]),
                            rdev  = np.std(df.xs(name,0)["Response"]),
                            rmin  = np.amin(df.xs(name,0)["Response"]),
                            rmax  = np.amax(df.xs(name,0)["Response"]),
                            # turnaround time stats
                            tmean = np.mean(df.xs(name,0)["Turnaround"]),
                            tdev  = np.std(df.xs(name,0)["Turnaround"]),
                            tmin  = np.amin(df.xs(name,0)["Turnaround"]),
                            tmax  = np.amax(df.xs(name,0)["Turnaround"]),
                            )
              )
        print("\n")

waits       = dict(list_waits(filenames(jim)))
responses   = dict(list_responses(filenames(jim)))
turnarounds = dict(list_turnarounds(filenames(jim)))

# Make box-and-whisker plots
sns.set(style="ticks")
with sns.palette_context('husl'):
    names = ["Priority",
             "Priority\n(preemptive)",
             "Round Robin",
             "Round Robin\n(prioritized)",
             "Shortest\nJob First",
             "Shortest\nJob First\n(preemptive)",
             "First Come,\nFirst Serve"]
    
    plt.figure(1, figsize=(9,6))
    plt.title("Wait times for various scheduling algorithms")
    
    sns.boxplot([waits['jim_priority.csv'],
                 waits['jim_priority-preemptive.csv'],
                 waits['jim_rr.csv'],
                 waits['jim_rr-pri.csv'],
                 waits['jim_sjf.csv'],
                 waits['jim_sjf-preemptive.csv'],
                 waits['jim_fcfs.csv']], 
                names=names)
    sns.axlabel("", "Wait time (CPU cycles)")
    sns.despine()
    
    plt.savefig(figpath + 'weller_whisker_wait.pdf')
    
    plt.figure(2, figsize=(9,6))
    plt.title("Response times for various scheduling algorithms")
    
    sns.boxplot([responses['jim_priority.csv'],
                 responses['jim_priority-preemptive.csv'],
                 responses['jim_rr.csv'],
                 responses['jim_rr-pri.csv'],
                 responses['jim_sjf.csv'],
                 responses['jim_sjf-preemptive.csv'],
                 responses['jim_fcfs.csv']], 
                names=names)
    
    sns.axlabel("", "Response time (CPU cycles)")
    sns.despine()
    
    plt.savefig(figpath + 'weller_whisker_response.pdf')
    
    plt.figure(3, figsize=(9,6))
    plt.title("Turnaround times for various scheduling algorithms")
    
    sns.boxplot([turnarounds['jim_priority.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_priority-preemptive.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_rr.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_rr-pri.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_sjf.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_sjf-preemptive.csv'],
                 turnarounds['jim_fcfs.csv']], 
                names=names)
        
    sns.axlabel("", "Turnaround time (CPU cycles)")
    sns.despine()
    
    plt.savefig(figpath + 'weller_whisker_turnaround.pdf')
